name: Kneeling Push-up
description: A scaled version of the normal push-up that works primarily the chest and triceps.

name: Regular Push-up
description: A classic calisthenic exercise that works the chest, triceps, shoulders, and core by raising and lowering the body towards the ground.

name: Diamond Push-up
description: A more challenging version of the push-up that works the tricps more than the regular version.

name: Bench Press
description: Increases upper-body pushing strength, explosiveness, and muscle growth. Can be done with a barbell or dumbbells.

name: Standing Flys
description: Focus on isolating the chest muscles by bringing weights in and squeezing the chest. Can be done laying on a bench if available.

name: Weighted Push-up
description: Make push-ups even more challenging by adding weight to your back. This can be done with a plate, backpack, or weighted vest.

name: Close Grip Bench Press
description: Bring your hands in to establish a narrow grip, and push up like a normal bench press. This will work your arms more than the normal version.

name: Single Leg Pushup
description: Normal pushup position, except on alternating pushups, keep one leg raised in the air.

name: Incline Bench Press
description: Lay on a bench angled at 30-45 deg. Push up dumbbells or barbell using your chest muscles.

name: Decline Bench Press
description: From a decline position, push the dumbbells or a barbell towards the ceiling using your chest muscles and squeezing at the top.

name: Alternating Shuffle Pushup
description: Do a standard push up, then at the top position, release your left hand, and plant it next to your right hand. Release your right hand and readjust to the right so your hands are shoulder width apart again.

name: Shoulder Taps
description: Works the deltoids, triceps, and core by forcing you to stabilize your body and touch your hand to the opposite shoulder.

name: Supermans
description: Simultaneously lift your arms, legs, and chest, and contract at the top of the movement. This exercise can be a good compliment to core movements.

name: Dips
description: Dips work your shoulders, arms, and chest, and can be done with a dip bar, bench, or chair.

name: Handstand Push-up
description: A very difficult gymnastics and strength move. Descend until the head touches the ground, brace the core, and push with the shoulders and arms.

name: Curls
description: Increase arm strength by doing curls with a barbell or dumbbells, bending at the elbow and concentrating on not swinging your body.

name: Shoulder Press
description: Can be performed either seated or standing, and can be done with a barbell or dumbbells. A great test over overhead pressing strength.

name: Pull-ups
description: A compound upper-body exercise with palms facing forward on the bar.

name: Triceps Push Down
description: Start with your torso straight, and bring the upper arms close to your body and perpendicular to the floor. Using the triceps, bring the rope down or bar down towards your sides.

name: Incline Dumbell Curl
description: Rest your arms on a bench angled at 45 degrees, then curl the dumbbells up, bending the elbows and bringing both weights to your shoulders.

name: Cross Body Hammer Curl
description: Keep your palms facing in and without twisting your arm, and curl the dumbbell of the right arm up towards your left shoulder. Repeat with each arm.

name: Overhead Press
description: Press arms upward until fully extended.  Be sure to engage the shoulders and triceps muscles.

name: Single Arm Resisted Curl
description: Place your left hand over your right fist, your left arm will provide the resistance for your right bicep. To perform a rep, simply try to bring your right fist up towards your right shoulder while you push down with your left arm.

name: Feet Elevated Pike Pushup
description: Get into pushup position and rest your feet on a bench or box. Bend your hips, raising your butt toward the ceiling so that your torso is vertical. Lower your body to the floor.

name: Crab Walk
description: Sit on the floor and plant your hands under your shoulders. Place your feet flat and bend your knees. Extend your hips so they rise an inch or so above the floor—this is crab position. Next, walk forward on your hands and feet

name: Glute Bridge
description: Strengthens the glutes, and increases glute activation with no equipment necessary.

name: Donkey Kickbacks
description: Targets each glute, and forced you to stabilize your core through the movement.

name: Calf Raises
description: This builds muscle and tones the calves by lifting as high as you can onto your toes.

name: Air Squats
description: A classic athletic exercise that works most of the lower body, and is the foundation for any workout program.

name: Single-leg Deadlifts
description: A great move that develops balance, as well as hamstring and glute strength.

name: Goblet Squats
description: Another  iation of the squat that works most of the lower body, and can be done with a  iety of different styles of weights.

name: Suitcase Deadlifts
description: A great move that works the hamstrings and glutes, while forcing you to stabilize the core.

name: Hamstring Drop
description: A glute and hamstring workout that also tests your core strength.

name: Elbow Plank Leg Raises
description: A glute and leg workout that has the benefit of giving your core a good push as well.

name: Squat Hold Calf Raises
description: Full leg workout that specifically targets your calves while still giving you a complete leg workout.

name: Side Kick with Bent Knee
description: A glute workout that also targets your hip flexors and core. Make sure to concentrate on your form.

name: Good Mornings
description: This workout targets your hamstrings, glutes, and lower back.

name: Split Squat
description: A tough single-leg move that will add size to your legs and improve balance.

name: Lunge
description: Single-leg exercise that works the quadriceps, but also works the glutes, hamstrings, and core muscles.

name: Box Jump
description: Great for improving athleticism and muscle that can become a challenging cardiovascular workout.

name: Jumping Lunges
description: Bring lunges to the next level by explosively jumping when transtioning between legs.

name: Pistol Squat
description: This advanced move requires flexibility, strength, balance, and coordination. This move can help build tremendous lower body strength.

name: Weighted Lunge
description: Single-leg exercise that works the quadriceps, but also works the glutes, hamstrings, and core muscles. Use dumbells, kettlebells, or whatever is available to you to add weight.

name: Weighted Side Lunges
description: Works the quads, glutes, adductors, and other smaller stabilizer muscles. Focus on collapsing at the hip and sitting into the lunge.

name: Weighted Jumping Lunge
description: Explode out of each lunge by jumping and switching legs, keeping the back straight, and controlling the descent of your rear knee to the ground.

name: Straight Leg Bounds
description: Leg exercise that works the quadriceps and has the benefit of being a cardio workout.

name: Jump Squats
description: Full leg exercise that mainly targets the quadriceps and gives you a good cardiovascular workout as well.

name: Reverse Plank Kicks
description: A full body exercise that targets your quadriceps and hip flexors.

name: Single Leg Squats
description: Single-leg exercise that targets all leg muscles, but specifically your quadriceps.

name: Crunches
description: A beginner exercise that helps strengthen the core.

name: Leg Raises
description: This exercise targets the abdominals and hip flexors, and will help to sculpt the core.

name: Plank
description: This static exercise works just about every muscle in the body, and helps to sculpt the core. Try 30 seconds if you're just starting out, or 1 minute if you're more experienced.

name: V-ups
description: Keep your legs straight and bring your upper body off of the floor to try and touch your toes. Great for targeting your middle and upper abs.

name: Russian Twist
description: This exercise strengthens the obliques, and can be performed with or without weight.

name: 3 point Plank
description: Start in a plank position with your body in a straight line. Lift your left leg up off the ground so that you are balancing on your right leg and both forearms. Hold for the desired amount of time and then switch legs so that your left leg is on the floor and your right is up in the air.

name: Dead Bug
description: Lie on your back and bend your hips and knees to a 90-degree angle. Extend your left leg toward the floor and bring your right arm overhead. Keep your abs tight and don't let your lower back arch. Return your arm and leg to the starting position.

name: Hanging Leg Raise
description: With your legs completely straight the entire time, tighten your core and use your abs to raise your feet toward your shoulders. Pause when your thighs reach your chest.

name: Cable Crunch
description: Keeping your weight on your knees and shins, let the cable pull on your arms and torso so that you feel a light stretch in your abdominal muscles. From there, crunch your body, bringing your forearms down to your knees and your head to the floor. Slowly return to the starting position.

name: Seated Barbell Twist
description: Place weight on your shoulders, keeping your back straight and upright. Twist your torso to the left, pause for a moment and then move back to the center.

name: Decline Crunch
description: Place your hands on either side of your head, without locking your fingers. Raise your body slowly while you contract your abs. Use a true decline bench, or something like a bench if you're at home.

name: Dumbbell Side Bend
description: Keeping your back straight and your eyes facing forwards, bend down to the right as far as you can, then back up again. Without pausing at the top, bend down to the left.

name: Jumping Jack
description: A classic performed by jumping from a position with legs together, and arms at the sides, to a position with legs apart and arms over head.

name: Bear Crawl
description: Increase your heart rate and stabilize your core by doing this fun exercise.

name: Mountain Climber
description: A great total body exercise that heavily utilizes the core, and can be a difficult cardiovascular exercise.

name: Spiderman Push-up
description: An advanced version of the push-up that will work the chest, triceps, shoulders, core, and hip flexors. Go slow and focus on the form.

name: Burpee
description: A great total body exercise that is performed in four steps, and can be a challenging cardiovascular exercise.

name: KettleBell Swings
description: Develops power in your hamstrings, glutes, core, and will get your heart rate up in no time. Focus on the hip hinge and being explosive.

name: Thrusters
description: Combines a front squat with an overhead press. A great compound exercise that works the whole body.

name: Single-arm Snatch
description: An advanced exercise that requires one fluid movement to take a dumbbell, kettlebell, or barbell from the ground to overhead.

name: Halo
description: While holding onto a kettlebell with both hands move it around your head.

name: Spider Walk
description: Walk froward while in raised push up position.

name: Lunge with overhead press
description: Hold weights at your sholders then go into a lunge pressing the weights up.

name: Renegade Row
description: While in raised push up position lift weights.

name: Figure Eight
description: Move kettlebell between legs in figure eight alternating the hand that holds it.

name: Back bow crossover
description: While facing the floor, raise legs and arms moving both left and right touching down at the end of each motion.
